Drop SeqID

In[]:
if "SeqID" in df.columns:
    df.drop(columns=["SeqID"], inplace=True)

Convert 'Date Of Stop' to 'Weekday'

In[]:
df["Date Of Stop"] = pd.to_datetime(df["Date Of Stop"], errors="coerce")
df["Weekday"] = df["Date Of Stop"].dt.weekday  # Monday=0, Sunday=6

Convert 'Time Of Stop' to 'Hour'

In[]:
df["Time Of Stop"] = pd.to_datetime(df["Time Of Stop"], format="%H:%M:%S", errors="coerce")
df["Hour"] = df["Time Of Stop"].dt.hour

Drop original datetime columns

In[]:
df.drop(columns=["Date Of Stop", "Time Of Stop"], inplace=True)

Drop irrelevant or redundant columns

In[]:
columns_to_drop = ["Agency", "SubAgency", "Description", "Location","Geolocation"]
df.drop(columns=columns_to_drop, inplace=True)

List of binary columns

In[]:
binary_cols = [
    "Accident", "Belts", "Personal Injury", "Property Damage", "Fatal",
    "Commercial License", "HAZMAT", "Commercial Vehicle", "Alcohol", "Work Zone"
]

df[binary_cols] = df[binary_cols].replace({"Yes": 'TRUE', "No": 'FALSE'})

Extract the code of reason to stop

In[]:
import pandas as pd

df['Search Reason For Stop'] = df['Search Reason For Stop'].str.extract(r'(\d{2})')
df['Charge'] = df['Charge'].str.extract(r'(\d{2})')

Fill blanks in all search-related fields with "NotApplicable"

In[]:
search_cols = [
    "Search Conducted",
    "Search Disposition",
    "Search Outcome",
    "Search Reason For Stop",
    "Search Reason",
    "Search Type",
    "Search Arrest Reason"
]

for col in search_cols:
    df[col] = df[col].fillna("NotApplicable")

Drop Rows Where Latitude or Longitude = 0

In[]:
df = df[(df['Latitude'] != 0) & (df['Longitude'] != 0)]

Drop rows with empty or missing 'Violation Type'

In[]:
df = df[df["Violation Type"].notna() & (df["Violation Type"] != "")]

Drop rows with empty or missing 'color'

In[]:
df = df[df["Color"].notna() & (df["Color"] != "")]

Then select the first 20,000 rows

In[]:
df = df.head(20200)

Remove numeric prefixes and keep just the descriptive label

In[]:
df['VehicleType'] = df['VehicleType'].str.replace(r'^\d+\s*-\s*', '', regex=True).str.strip()

def categorize_year(y):
    if y >= 2015:
        return 'Recent'
    elif y >= 2005:
        return '2005-2014'
    elif y >= 1995:
        return '1995-2004'
    elif y >= 1985:
        return '1985-1994'
    else:
        return 'Old'
df['YearGroup'] = df['Year'].apply(categorize_year)
df.drop(columns='Year', inplace=True)
In[]:
def categorize_hour(h):
    if 5 <= h <= 11:
        return 'Morning'
    elif 12 <= h <= 16:
        return 'Afternoon'
    elif 17 <= h <= 20:
        return 'Evening'
    else:
        return 'Night'
df['HourGroup'] = df['Hour'].apply(categorize_hour)
df.drop(columns='Hour', inplace=True)

In[]:
def group_stop_reason(code):
    if code.startswith('21'):
        return 'Traffic'
    elif code.startswith('16'):
        return 'License'
    elif code.startswith('22'):
        return 'Equipment'
    elif code.startswith('13'):
        return 'Registration'
    elif code.startswith('11'):
        return 'Commercial'
    elif code.startswith('14'):
        return 'Behavior'
    elif code.startswith('17'):
        return 'Speeding'
    elif code in ['23', '24', '25', '20']:
        return 'Misc'
    elif code in ['55', '56', '59', '61', '64', '65', '88', '89']:
        return 'Other'
    else:
        return 'NotApplicable'

df['SearchReasonGroup'] = df['Search Reason For Stop'].apply(group_stop_reason)
df.drop(columns='Search Reason For Stop', inplace=True)

# Convert numpy arrays (or pandas) to PyTorch tensors
X_train_tensor = torch.tensor(X_train.values, dtype=torch.float32)

batch_size = 64

train_dataset = TensorDataset(X_train_tensor, y_train_tensor)
val_dataset = TensorDataset(X_val_tensor, y_val_tensor)
test_dataset = TensorDataset(X_test_tensor, y_test_tensor)

train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset, batch_size=batch_size, shuffle=True)
val_loader = DataLoader(val_dataset, batch_size=batch_size)
test_loader = DataLoader(test_dataset, batch_size=batch_size)

Define the Neural Network Architecture

In[]:
class ShallowNN(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden1=128, hidden2=64, output_size=3):
        super(ShallowNN, self).__init__()
        self.net = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(input_size, hidden1),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(0.3),
            nn.Linear(hidden1, hidden2),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout(0.3),
            nn.Linear(hidden2, output_size)
        )

    def forward(self, x):
        return self.net(x)

# Initialize model
input_size = X_train.shape[1]
output_size = len(np.unique(y_train))
model = ShallowNN(input_size=input_size, output_size=output_size).to(device)

Set Loss Function & Optimizer

In[]:
criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()
optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)

from torch.optim.lr_scheduler import ReduceLROnPlateau

scheduler = ReduceLROnPlateau(optimizer, mode='min', factor=0.5, patience=3, verbose=True)

Training Loop (Basic Version)

In[]:
import time

num_epochs = 30
train_losses, val_losses = [], []
train_accuracies, val_accuracies = [], []

start_time = time.time()

for epoch in range(num_epochs):
    model.train()
    total_train_loss = 0
    correct_train = 0

    for batch_X, batch_y in train_loader:
        batch_X, batch_y = batch_X.to(device), batch_y.to(device)

        optimizer.zero_grad()
        outputs = model(batch_X)
        loss = criterion(outputs, batch_y)
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()

        total_train_loss += loss.item()
        _, preds = torch.max(outputs, 1)
        correct_train += (preds == batch_y).sum().item()

    train_loss = total_train_loss / len(train_loader)
    train_acc = correct_train / len(train_loader.dataset)

    # Validation
    model.eval()
    total_val_loss = 0
    correct_val = 0

    with torch.no_grad():
        for val_X, val_y in val_loader:
            val_X, val_y = val_X.to(device), val_y.to(device)
            val_outputs = model(val_X)
            val_loss = criterion(val_outputs, val_y)
            total_val_loss += val_loss.item()
            _, val_preds = torch.max(val_outputs, 1)
            correct_val += (val_preds == val_y).sum().item()

    val_loss = total_val_loss / len(val_loader)
    val_acc = correct_val / len(val_loader.dataset)

    # Store metrics
    train_losses.append(train_loss)
    val_losses.append(val_loss)
    train_accuracies.append(train_acc)
    val_accuracies.append(val_acc)
    scheduler.step(val_loss)


    print(f"Epoch {epoch+1}/{num_epochs} | "
          f"Train Loss: {train_loss:.4f} | Val Loss: {val_loss:.4f} | "
          f"Train Acc: {train_acc:.4f} | Val Acc: {val_acc:.4f}")

end_time = time.time()
print(f"\nTraining complete in {end_time - start_time:.2f} seconds.")
